""

#. HTML: <section id="vagga"><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.52" id="52"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an2.52-63:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 2 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 2 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:0.2"
msgid "6. Puggalavagga "
msgstr "6. Persons "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:0.3"
msgid "52 "
msgstr "52 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc52.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:52.1.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, puggalā loke uppajjamānā uppajjanti bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya, bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ. "
msgstr "“Two people, mendicants, arise in the world for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:52.1.2"
msgid "Katame dve? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:52.1.3"
msgid "Tathāgato ca arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, rājā ca cakkavattī. "
msgstr "The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha; and the wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:52.1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve puggalā loke uppajjamānā uppajjanti bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya, bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti. "
msgstr "These two people arise in the world for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.53" id="53"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:52.1.5"
msgid "53 "
msgstr "53 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.77, sc53.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:53.1.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, puggalā loke uppajjamānā uppajjanti acchariyamanussā. "
msgstr "“Two people, mendicants, arise in the world who are incredible human beings. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:53.1.2"
msgid "Katame dve? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:53.1.3"
msgid "Tathāgato ca arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, rājā ca cakkavattī. "
msgstr "The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha; and the wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:53.1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve puggalā loke uppajjamānā uppajjanti acchariyamanussā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the two people who arise in the world who are incredible human beings.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.54" id="54"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:53.1.5"
msgid "54 "
msgstr "54 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc54.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:54.1.1"
msgid "“Dvinnaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalānaṃ kālakiriyā bahuno janassa anutappā hoti. "
msgstr "“There are two people, mendicants, whose death is regretted by many people. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:54.1.2"
msgid "Katamesaṃ dvinnaṃ? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:54.1.3"
msgid "Tathāgatassa ca arahato sammāsambuddhassa, rañño ca cakkavattissa. "
msgstr "The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha; and the wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:54.1.4"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ kālakiriyā bahuno janassa anutappā hotī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the two people, mendicants, whose death is regretted by many people.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.55" id="55"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:54.1.5"
msgid "55 "
msgstr "55 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc55.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:55.1.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, thūpārahā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these two are worthy of a monument. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:55.1.2"
msgid "Katame dve? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:55.1.3"
msgid "Tathāgato ca arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, rājā ca cakkavattī. "
msgstr "The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha; and the wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:55.1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve thūpārahā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the two who are worthy of a monument.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.56" id="56"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:55.1.5"
msgid "56 "
msgstr "56 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc56.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:56.1.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, buddhā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are two kinds of Buddhas. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:56.1.2"
msgid "Katame dve? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:56.1.3"
msgid "Tathāgato ca arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, paccekabuddho ca. "
msgstr "The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha; and the Buddha awakened for themselves. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:56.1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve buddhā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the two kinds of Buddhas.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.57" id="57"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:56.1.5"
msgid "57 "
msgstr "57 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc57.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:57.1.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, asaniyā phalantiyā na santasanti. "
msgstr "“These two, mendicants, are not startled by a crack of thunder. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:57.1.2"
msgid "Katame dve? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:57.1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhu ca khīṇāsavo, hatthājānīyo ca. "
msgstr "A mendicant who has ended defilements; and a thoroughbred elephant. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:57.1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve asaniyā phalantiyā na santasantī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the two who are not startled by a crack of thunder.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.58" id="58"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:57.1.5"
msgid "58 "
msgstr "58 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc58.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:58.1.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, asaniyā phalantiyā na santasanti. "
msgstr "“These two, mendicants, are not startled by a crack of thunder. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:58.1.2"
msgid "Katame dve? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:58.1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhu ca khīṇāsavo, assājānīyo ca. "
msgstr "A mendicant who has ended defilements; and a thoroughbred horse. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:58.1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve asaniyā phalantiyā na santasantī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the two who are not startled by a crack of thunder.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.59" id="59"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:58.1.5"
msgid "59 "
msgstr "59 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc59.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:59.1.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, asaniyā phalantiyā na santasanti. "
msgstr "“These two, mendicants, are not startled by a crack of thunder. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:59.1.2"
msgid "Katame dve? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:59.1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhu ca khīṇāsavo, sīho ca migarājā. "
msgstr "A mendicant who has ended defilements; and a lion, king of beasts. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:59.1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve asaniyā phalantiyā na santasantī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the two who are not startled by a crack of thunder.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.60" id="60"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:59.1.5"
msgid "60 "
msgstr "60 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc60.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:60.1.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, atthavase sampassamānā kiṃpurisā mānusiṃ vācaṃ na bhāsanti. "
msgstr "“Fauns see two reasons not to use human speech. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:60.1.2"
msgid "Katame dve? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:60.1.3"
msgid "Mā ca musā bhaṇimhā, mā ca paraṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhimhāti. "
msgstr "Thinking: ‘May we not lie, and may we not misrepresent others with falsehoods.’ "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:60.1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve atthavase sampassamānā kiṃpurisā mānusiṃ vācaṃ na bhāsantī”ti. "
msgstr "Fauns see two reasons not to use human speech.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.61" id="61"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:60.1.5"
msgid "61 "
msgstr "61 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.78, sc61.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:61.1.1"
msgid "“Dvinnaṃ dhammānaṃ, bhikkhave, atitto appaṭivāno mātugāmo kālaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, females die without getting enough of two things. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:61.1.2"
msgid "Katamesaṃ dvinnaṃ? "
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:61.1.3"
msgid "Methunasamāpattiyā ca vijāyanassa ca. "
msgstr "Sexual intercourse and giving birth. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:61.1.4"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dvinnaṃ dhammānaṃ atitto appaṭivāno mātugāmo kālaṃ karotī”ti. "
msgstr "Females die without getting enough of these two things.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.62" id="62"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:61.1.5"
msgid "62 "
msgstr "62 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc62.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.1.1"
msgid "“Asantasannivāsañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi santasannivāsañca. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you about living with bad people and living with good people. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.1.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.1.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.79, sc62.2
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.1"
msgid "“Kathañca, bhikkhave, asantasannivāso hoti, kathañca asanto sannivasanti? "
msgstr "“What is it like living with bad people? How do bad people live together? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, therassa bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "It’s when a senior mendicant thinks: "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.3"
msgid "‘theropi maṃ na vadeyya, majjhimopi maṃ na vadeyya, navopi maṃ na vadeyya; "
msgstr "‘No mendicant, whether senior, middle, or junior, should admonish me; "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.4"
msgid "therampāhaṃ na vadeyyaṃ, majjhimampāhaṃ na vadeyyaṃ, navampāhaṃ na vadeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "and I shouldn’t admonish any mendicant, whether senior, middle, or junior. "

#. VAR: viheṭheyyaṃ → viheseyyampi naṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.5"
msgid "Thero cepi maṃ vadeyya ahitānukampī maṃ vadeyya no hitānukampī, noti naṃ vadeyyaṃ viheṭheyyaṃ passampissa nappaṭikareyyaṃ. "
msgstr "If a mendicant—whether senior, middle, or junior—were to admonish me, they wouldn’t be sympathetic, and I’d bother them by saying “No!” And anyway I wouldn’t deal with it even if I saw what I did wrong.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.6"
msgid "Majjhimo cepi maṃ vadeyya … pe … navo cepi maṃ vadeyya, ahitānukampī maṃ vadeyya no hitānukampī, noti naṃ vadeyyaṃ viheṭheyyaṃ passampissa nappaṭikareyyaṃ’. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.7"
msgid "Majjhimassapi bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti … pe … navassapi bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And a middle or a junior mendicant also thinks: "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.8"
msgid "‘theropi maṃ na vadeyya, majjhimopi maṃ na vadeyya, navopi maṃ na vadeyya; "
msgstr "‘No mendicant, whether senior, middle, or junior, should admonish me; "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.9"
msgid "therampāhaṃ na vadeyyaṃ, majjhimampāhaṃ na vadeyyaṃ, navampāhaṃ na vadeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "and I shouldn’t admonish any mendicant, whether senior, middle, or junior. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.10"
msgid "Thero cepi maṃ vadeyya ahitānukampī maṃ vadeyya no hitānukampī noti naṃ vadeyyaṃ viheṭheyyaṃ passampissa nappaṭikareyyaṃ. "
msgstr "If a mendicant—whether senior, middle, or junior—were to admonish me, they wouldn’t be sympathetic, and I’d bother them by saying “No!” And anyway I wouldn’t deal with it even if I saw what I did wrong.’ "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.11"
msgid "Majjhimo cepi maṃ vadeyya … navo cepi maṃ vadeyya ahitānukampī maṃ vadeyya no hitānukampī, noti naṃ vadeyyaṃ viheṭheyyaṃ passampissa nappaṭikareyyaṃ’. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.2.12"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, asantasannivāso hoti, evañca asanto sannivasanti. "
msgstr "That’s what it’s like living with bad people; that’s how bad people live together. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc62.3
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, santasannivāso hoti, kathañca santo sannivasanti? "
msgstr "What is it like living with good people? How do good people live together? "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, therassa bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "It’s when a senior mendicant thinks: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.3"
msgid "‘theropi maṃ vadeyya, majjhimopi maṃ vadeyya, navopi maṃ vadeyya; "
msgstr "‘Any mendicant, whether senior, middle, or junior, should admonish me; "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.4"
msgid "therampāhaṃ vadeyyaṃ, majjhimampāhaṃ vadeyyaṃ, navampāhaṃ vadeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "and I should admonish any mendicant, whether senior, middle, or junior. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.5"
msgid "Thero cepi maṃ vadeyya hitānukampī maṃ vadeyya no ahitānukampī, sādhūti naṃ vadeyyaṃ na naṃ viheṭheyyaṃ passampissa paṭikareyyaṃ. "
msgstr "If a mendicant—whether senior, middle, or junior—were to admonish me, they’d be sympathetic, so I wouldn’t bother them, but say “Thank you!” And I’d deal with it when I saw what I did wrong.’ "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.6"
msgid "Majjhimo cepi maṃ vadeyya … pe … navo cepi maṃ vadeyya hitānukampī maṃ vadeyya no ahitānukampī, sādhūti naṃ vadeyyaṃ na naṃ viheṭheyyaṃ passampissa paṭikareyyaṃ’. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.7"
msgid "Majjhimassapi bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti … pe … navassapi bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And a middle or a junior mendicant also thinks: "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.8"
msgid "‘theropi maṃ vadeyya, majjhimopi maṃ vadeyya, navopi maṃ vadeyya; "
msgstr "‘Any mendicant, whether senior, middle, or junior, may admonish me; "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.9"
msgid "therampāhaṃ vadeyyaṃ, majjhimampāhaṃ vadeyyaṃ, navampāhaṃ vadeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "and I’ll admonish any mendicant, whether senior, middle, or junior. "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.10"
msgid "Thero cepi maṃ vadeyya hitānukampī maṃ vadeyya no ahitānukampī, sādhūti naṃ vadeyyaṃ na naṃ viheṭheyyaṃ passampissa paṭikareyyaṃ. "
msgstr "If a mendicant—whether senior, middle, or junior—were to admonish me, they’d be sympathetic, so I wouldn’t bother them, but say “Thank you!” And I’d deal with it when I saw what I did wrong.’ "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.11"
msgid "Majjhimo cepi maṃ vadeyya … pe … navo cepi maṃ vadeyya hitānukampī maṃ vadeyya no ahitānukampī, sādhūti naṃ vadeyyaṃ na naṃ viheṭheyyaṃ passampissa paṭikareyyaṃ’. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.12"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, santasannivāso hoti, evañca santo sannivasantī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what it’s like living with good people; that’s how good people live together.” "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an2.63" id="63"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an2.52-63:62.3.13"
msgid "63 "
msgstr "63 "

# NOTE: Var readings vacisamhara, vacisamsara, vacisankhara: MN 103 Comm: Vacīsaṃhāroti vacanasañcāro. Imehi kathitaṃ amūsaṃ antaraṃ paveseyya, tumhe imehi idañcidañca vuttāti amūhi kathitaṃ imesaṃ antaraṃ paveseyyāti attho, Tika: Vacanasañcāroti pesuññavasena aññathāvacanupasaṃhāro. The parallel passage is at AN 2.63, where samsara is the MS reading, and adopted by BB there. Comm there gives a completely different explanation: ubhato vacīsaṃsāroti dvīsupi pakkhesu aññamaññaṃ akkosanapaccakkosanavasena saṃsaramānā vācā vacīsaṃsāro. Tika has: Saṃsaramānāti pavattamānā. Despite this, I think the reading samhara makes better sense, as per MN comm.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.80, sc63.1
msgctxt "an2.52-63:63.1.1"
msgid "“Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇe ubhato vacīsaṃsāro diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo anabhiraddhi ajjhattaṃ avūpasantaṃ hoti, tasmetaṃ, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇe pāṭikaṅkhaṃ: "
msgstr "“In a disciplinary issue, when the tale-bearing on both sides—with contempt for each other’s views, resentful, bitter, and exasperated—is not settled internally, you can expect that this disciplinary issue will be "

#. VAR: phāsuṃ → phāsu (mr)
msgctxt "an2.52-63:63.1.2"
msgid "‘dīghattāya kharattāya vāḷattāya saṃvattissati, bhikkhū ca na phāsuṃ viharissanti’. "
msgstr "long, fractious, and troublesome, and the mendicants won’t live comfortably. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc63.2
msgctxt "an2.52-63:63.2.1"
msgid "Yasmiñca kho, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇe ubhato vacīsaṃsāro diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo anabhiraddhi ajjhattaṃ suvūpasantaṃ hoti, tasmetaṃ, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇe pāṭikaṅkhaṃ: "
msgstr "In a disciplinary issue, when the tale-bearing on both sides—with contempt for each other’s views, resentful, bitter, and exasperated—is well settled internally, you can expect that this disciplinary issue "

msgctxt "an2.52-63:63.2.2"
msgid "‘na dīghattāya kharattāya vāḷattāya saṃvattissati, bhikkhū ca phāsuṃ viharissantī’”ti. "
msgstr "won’t lead to lasting acrimony and enmity, and the mendicants will live comfortably.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an2.52-63:63.2.3"
msgid "Puggalavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></section></body></html>
